Text.string: Vault Hunter. I require assistance.
I'm running short on syringes.

Honestly, I wonder sometimes why I put up with all of this! Though, I suppose it does provide me with access to plenty of Eridian artifacts, and a ready supply of test subjects. Oh, right. I'm supposed to call them “patients”.
I can finally get back to work now. Thank you, Vault Hunter. And if you discover anyone else has stolen my syringes, please execute them. Okay. Bye!
Now how in the hell did that even get up there?
Well... that was just spectacularly unsafe.
You found it where?! Unbelievable.
Honestly, what were they thinking?
Well that's just ridiculous.
Why? Just... why?!
Why would anyone do THAT with a syringe?
Unbelievable!
It would appear that the idiotic primate inhabitants of this vessel have been stealing my syringes and using them for who-knows-what. I'm running low and I need them back!
Ugh. How could they?
Hgh. Idiots.
Someone actually stole one of my syringes, to do—to do... THAT? W-With... Okay.
Can't these people find some other way to amuse themselves?

Do these neanderthals not understand that I need to keep this laboratory stocked in order to do my job? Without syringes, how am I supposed to move various liquids from one place to another? Unbelievable.
Using my syringes for a dart game?! Unacceptable! Besides, everyone knows games are for addle-brained simpletons and impudent children.
Oh, wonderful. That one was used to cover up borderline pornography. Hnh. Puritanical notions of sexuality are so last century.
Why are we still picking up transmissions through antennae anyway?! It's barbaric! We live in the future, damn it!
Using my syringe for something as base as food preparation?! This ship is full of animals and savages!
Well, hard to argue with that one, haha! Claptrap does need a good kicking. But then again, so many things do.
That's probably all you're going to find. Please bring them back to me so I may continue my work, Vault Hunter.
